{
  "stem": "14168.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "So in 1935, I took my high school leaving examination.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "I got a very good grade.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "It was in French and History, and I had to give a discourse in French on the French Naturalist [INAUDIBLE] and other French philosophers.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And in 1935, right afterwards, I entered the Jewish a seminary-- theological seminary, because I wanted to become a rabbi.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Breslau.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Breslau had the oldest rabbinical school-- theological seminary in Germany.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It had been founded in 1853.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And as I said before, I believe, it had the distinction of a staff of professors who made history in-- in the world of-- of Jewish learning.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We had-- of course we studied the Talmud, but at the same time, philosophy and psychology.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And it was a tremendous experience.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, there was one philosopher that interested me very much and interests me up to this day.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "That was Baruch Spinoza.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And the professor who acquainted us with his teachings also said that, of course, from a Jewish theological standpoint, he was not accepted.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But I got fascinated by him, and we had the learned-- the professor Heinemann, Isaac Heinemann.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "A blessed memory.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "He then, later on, went to Israel and taught there.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And he was a scholarly man.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "He was at home both in Greek philosophy and the Greek language and in-- of course, in Talmudic-- in the world of the Talmud.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, my experiences at the seminary [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] were a-- were one of the-- in fact, I would say this-- this seminary-- my attendance at the seminary belongs to one of the most interesting, creative, seminal experiences in my life, because I had at the-- I was exposed to a tremendous variety of scholarly people.",
      "word_count": 57
    }
  ],
